Java class 8
Loops in Java:

WHILE-when we dont know the number of repetition(Checks condition first Then executes code
while (boolean condition){
code to repeat;
}while (boolean condition);


DO WHILE-when we dont know the number of repetition(Executes code first then Checks condition
do{
  code to repeat
  
}

FOR-when we known number of repetitions/iterations
for(initialization;condition;increments/decrements
ENHANCED for loop/for each loop/ advanced for looop
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Nested loops-loops inside another loop
 
 for(int i=1; i<3; i++){
 system.put.println("Hello");
 
 for(j=1; j<=3; j++){------>nested loop
   system.out.println("Bye")
   }
  }